<paragraph id="C15FC41E3A01FFE270F6E8094CDCD286" blockId="3.[151,1436,1817,2036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
Primary thallus persistent, consisting of 
<quantity id="061869FB3A01FFE2721AE8094D87D241" box="[635,733,1817,1843]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4 mm</quantity>
long, horizontal to ascending squamules which are deeply divided in ca. 0.5–1.0 mm wide and ca. 
<quantity id="061869FB3A01FFE2721FE8504D83D228" box="[638,729,1856,1882]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
thick, slightly crenulate lobes, with flat to concave, green upper side and white or pale brown, shiny lower side, with pale hypothallus, often isidiate along the tips of erect, up to 
<quantity id="061869FB3A01FFE27145E89D4E33D2D5" box="[292,361,1933,1959]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity id="061869FB3A01FFE27181E89D4D7ED2D5" box="[480,548,1933,1959]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
wide extensions of the lobes; isidia short-cylindrical, ca. 
<quantity id="061869FB3A01FFE274B3E89D4A77D2D5" box="[1234,1325,1933,1959]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity id="061869FB3A01FFE270F6E8A44E5BD2BC" box="[151,257,1972,1998]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="0.15">0.15 mm</quantity>
wide, glossy. Podetia, conidiomata and hymenial discs not known. Chemistry: barbatic and 4-Odemethylbarbatic (minor) acids. Colour reactions: P–, K–, KC–.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
