<subSubSection id="89FA97953A06FFE570A7EA534BE8D08A" pageId="4" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C15FC41E3A06FFE570A7EA534BE8D08A" blockId="4.[151,1436,1231,1528]" pageId="4" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="F394180C3A06FFE570A7EA534E05D02F" bold="true" box="[198,351,1347,1373]" pageId="4" pageNumber="29">Remarks:—</emphasis>
The presence of cylindrical isidia is so unusual in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="06E0BF9D3A06FFE57447EA534BC9D02E" box="[1062,1171,1347,1372]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Cladoniaceae" genus="Cladonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="4" pageNumber="29" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F394180C3A06FFE57447EA534BC9D02E" box="[1062,1171,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="29">Cladonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, that there is no doubt that the only available specimen belongs to an undescribed species. The thallus squamules show that it is related to 
<taxonomicName id="06E0BF9D3A06FFE5716CEA814ED3D0D8" authorityName="G. Meyer" authorityYear="1825" box="[269,393,1425,1450]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Cladoniaceae" genus="Cladonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="4" pageNumber="29" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="miniata">
<emphasis id="F394180C3A06FFE5716CEA814ED3D0D8" box="[269,393,1425,1450]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="29">C. miniata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Morphologically it bears most similarity with 
<taxonomicName id="06E0BF9D3A06FFE573DBEA814B48D0D8" authorityName="S. Stenroos" authorityYear="1989" box="[954,1042,1425,1450]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Cladoniaceae" genus="Cladonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="4" pageNumber="29" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ahtii">
<emphasis id="F394180C3A06FFE573DBEA814B48D0D8" box="[954,1042,1425,1450]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="29">C. ahtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species is sorediate instead of isidiate, and it lacks the peculiar lobe extensions. In the 
<taxonomicName id="06E0BF9D3A06FFE57322EAA84CE4D0A3" authorityName="G. Meyer" authorityYear="1825" box="[835,958,1464,1489]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Cladoniaceae" genus="Cladonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="4" pageNumber="29" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="miniata">
<emphasis id="F394180C3A06FFE57322EAA84CE4D0A3" box="[835,958,1464,1489]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="29">C. miniata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group there is one more isidiate species, 
<taxonomicName id="06E0BF9D3A06FFE570F6EACE4D18D08A" authority="S. Stenroos (1989: 256)" authorityName="S. Stenroos" authorityPageNumber="256" authorityYear="1989" box="[151,578,1502,1528]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Cladoniaceae" genus="Cladonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="4" pageNumber="29" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="caribaea">
<emphasis id="F394180C3A06FFE570F6EACE4E7BD085" box="[151,289,1502,1527]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="29">C. caribaea</emphasis>
S. 
<bibRefCitation id="A571B9EF3A06FFE57126EACE4D18D08A" author="Stenroos, S." box="[327,578,1502,1528]" pageId="4" pageNumber="29" pagination="237 - 261" refId="ref7246" refString="Stenroos, S. (1989) Taxonomic revision of the Cladonia miniata group. Annales Botanici Fennici 26: 237 - 261." type="journal article" year="1989">Stenroos (1989: 256)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. This has coralloid to flattened, not cylindrical isidia.
</paragraph>
